NOTE on bundled musical works:

The 50 melodies bundled in `src/data/songs.ts` are NOT covered by the MIT
license above. They are simplified single-line arrangements of works that
are in the public domain in Japan and most other jurisdictions:

  - Traditional / folk songs (London Bridge, Twinkle Twinkle, etc.)
  - Christmas carols and hymns (Silent Night by F. Gruber 1818,
    Auld Lang Syne, Amazing Grace, etc.)
  - Classical works whose composers died more than 70 years ago
    (J.S. Bach, Mozart, Beethoven, Chopin, Schubert, Brahms,
    Tchaikovsky, Debussy, Satie, Elgar, etc.)
  - "Happy Birthday to You" — entered the U.S. public domain in 2016
    after the Hill sisters' copyright was invalidated, and is treated
    as public domain in Japan under the WTO TRIPS framework.

These arrangements are themselves released into the public domain
(Creative Commons Zero / CC0). You may freely copy, modify, and
redistribute them.

If you believe any bundled melody infringes a copyright in your
jurisdiction, please open an issue and it will be removed promptly.
